The paper analyzes trends in research output indexed in Scopus and Web of Science, which are databases commonly used in computer science research. The breakdown of numbers by document type, publication language, research discipline, and source suggests that the paper may be relevant to several sub-categories, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
